    "text": "Hey there, homemakers. I'm here to tell you about Hefty's new plastic scrap bags. They've finally solved the problem of what to do with wet kitchen scraps. Just set one on its own little stand and then stuff it with all the wet nasties that used to sop through the bag on the way to the garbage can. When it's full, just tear, tie, and toss it away. Dry as a bone. New leaf-proof Hefty scrap bags. You'll get some here and tie one on Bramante. Ha, ha, ha, ha, ha. Yeah. New Hefty. Hefty scrap bags from Mobile. And don't forget, when garbage starts piling up on you, use Hefty trash can liners and wrap up the problem. Big, strong Hefty liners are leak-proof, odor-proof, plastic. And leave the container clean so one can can do the work of more. Hefty. Hefty trash can liners. Use them. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty. Hefty.",
